 DAY I HIGHLIGHTS
 India are hosting a Test after nearly a year and eight months. The last Test on Indian soil was against England in Mumbai, March 18, 2006  Anil Kumble became the 30th Indian to lead in Tests. He is the third from Karnataka after Gundappa Viswanath and Rahul Dravid  Pakistans trouble with opening partnerships continue. They last had a 100-plus opening stand against India, in the third Test in Karachi (January 2006). In that match, Salman Butt and Imran Farhat stitched 109 runs. Since then the visitors have played 14 Tests. Their highest opening partnership in this period has been 90 (Butt and Kamran Akmal) versus South Africa in Lahore (October 2007)  Shoaib Malik became the first Pakistan captain to record a duck in a Test in India  Kumbles dismissal of Akmal was his 50th scalp at the Kotla. For the record, Sri Lanka off-spinner Muttiah Muralidharan holds the record for most wickets at a venue. He has bagged 143 wickets at the SSC Ground, Colombo  Misbah-ul Haq recorded his highest Test score, surpassing his 41 against South Africa in Lahore, October 2007 COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON 
